ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Hokkaido is know to be endemic for _E.multilocularis_, and the
reservoir is the red fox (_Vulpes vulpes schrencki_) and raccoon dog
(_Nyctereutes procyonoides albus_). Bait-delivered anthelmintic to
reduce the prevalence in wild red foxes has been tried but with
inconclusive results. It is alarming that domestic dogs may become
infected and excrete eggs in the domestic environment, in theory
increasing the likelihood that humans may become infected. - Mod.EP]
[Echinococcosis is an OIE List B disease. Diagnostic methods in
animal hosts are described in chapter 2.2.3 of their manual of
standards, diagnostic tests and vaccines
<http://www.oie.int/eng/normes/mmanual/A_00040.htm> - Mod.AS]
